The paper deals with image analysis and deep learning, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of steerable filters and spherical harmonics suggests a focus on mathematical methods and algorithms, which could also place the paper in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the evaluation of the proposed methods on 3D datasets suggests a potential fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category, while the use of CT scans for pulmonary nodule classification could also place the paper in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
